# Yorkies (No-Fail Popovers)

Andrea Geary's foolproof popovers from America's Test Kitchen — crisp and deep golden brown on the outside, hollow and custardy inside. No preheating the pan and no special equipment required; bread flour and warm milk do the heavy lifting.

*bread, breakfast, brunch, side*

**6 popovers**

---

- *191 grams* bread flour
- *3/4 teaspoon* table salt
- *1 1/2 cups* 2% low-fat milk, heated to 110 to 120 degrees (microwave until hot to the touch)
- *3* large eggs

---

1. Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 400 degrees (convection). Lightly spray cups of popover pan with vegetable oil spray.
2. Whisk together flour and salt in 8-cup liquid measuring cup or medium bowl. Add milk and eggs and whisk until mostly smooth (some small lumps are OK). Distribute batter evenly among prepared cups in popover pan.
3. Bake until popovers are lofty and deep golden brown all over, 40 to 45 minutes. Serve hot, passing butter separately.

**Note:** This batter comes together quickly, so start heating your oven before gathering ingredients. Works best in a 6-cup popover pan, but a 12-cup muffin tin can be substituted — distribute batter among all 12 cups and start checking after 25 minutes. Whole or skim milk can replace the low-fat milk.
